# üöÄ JMA Field Trip Management System

A comprehensive, FERPA-compliant field trip management system built specifically for JMA Middle School and Charlotte-Mecklenburg Schools.

**One Mission, Many Places & Endless Possibilities**

## ‚ú® Features

- **7-Stage Approval Workflow** - Streamlined approval from staff to cafeteria
- **Real-time Email Notifications** - Automated alerts at 7:00 AM and 12:00 PM daily  
- **Admin Notes System** - Complete communication tracking throughout approval
- **Report Generation** - Comprehensive trip reports, volunteer lists, health info
- **Mobile Responsive** - Works perfectly on any device
- **FERPA Compliant** - Secure handling of all student and staff data
- **Role-Based Access** - 8 different user roles with appropriate permissions
- **Cost-Free Forever** - Built on free tier services with no ongoing costs

## üöÄ Quick Deploy

[![Deploy with Vercel](https://vercel.com/button)](https://vercel.com/new/clone?repository-url=https://github.com/your-username/jma-field-trip-system&env=NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL,NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY,RESEND_API_KEY&envDescription=Required%20environment%20variables&envLink=https://github.com/your-username/jma-field-trip-system#environment-variables)

## üõ†Ô∏è Manual Setup

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ 
- [Supabase account](https://supabase.com) (free)
- [Vercel account](https://vercel.com) (free) 
- [Resend account](https://resend.com) (free)
- [GitHub account](https://github.com) (free)

### Step 1: Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/jma-field-trip-system.git
cd jma-field-trip-system
npm install
```

### Step 2: Database Setup

1. **Create Supabase Project**
   - Go to [supabase.com](https://supabase.com)
   - Click "New Project"
   - Name: "JMA Field Trips"
   - Choose region closest to North Carolina

2. **Run Database Script**
   - Go to Supabase ‚Üí SQL Editor
   - Copy contents of `supabase/setup.sql`
   - Paste and click "Run"

3. **Get API Keys**
   - Go to Settings ‚Üí API
   - Copy "Project URL" and "anon public" key

### Step 3: Environment Variables

Create `.env.local` file:

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
RESEND_API_KEY=your_resend_api_key

# Optional customization
NEXT_PUBLIC_SCHOOL_NAME="JMA Middle School"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SCHOOL_DOMAIN="cms.k12.nc.us"
NEXT_PUBLIC_PRINCIPAL_NAME="Principal Hager"
```

### Step 4: Email Setup

1. **Get Resend API Key**
   - Go to [resend.com](https://resend.com)
   - Create account ‚Üí API Keys ‚Üí Create
   - Copy the key to your `.env.local`

### Step 5: Development

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

### Step 6: Deploy to Production

1. **Push to GitHub**
   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial JMA Field Trip System"
   git push origin main
   ```

2. **Deploy to Vercel**
   - Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com)
   - Import GitHub repository
   - Add environment variables
   - Deploy!

## üì± User Roles & Access

### Staff Members
- Submit pre-approval forms
- Track request status
- View own requests only

### Front Office Administrators  
- Review calendar availability
- Approve/deny date requests
- Manage master school calendar

### Principal & Assistant Principals
